Intel will reveal its 8th-generation Core desktop processors on 21 August 2017. The announcement will be streamed on Facebook Live at 17:00 SAST. Intel’s new chips are code-named Coffee Lake and will be built on the same 14nm manufacturing process as its last two generations of desktop processors – boasting performance improvements and possibly an increased core count. According to Intel, customers will be able to purchase devices with 8th-gen Core processors during the holiday season.